title: Thailand Three Month Interbank Rate
description: Thailand Three Month Interbank Rate increased to 1.29 percent on Tuesday November 8 from 1.28 percent in the previous day. Interbank Rate in Thailand averaged 2.28 percent from 2005 until 2022, reaching an all time high of 5.41 percent in July of 2006 and a record low of 0.62 percent in August of 2021. The interbank rate is the rate of interest charged on short-term loans made between banks in the local currency. This page provides - Thailand Interbank Rate- actual values, historical data, forecast, chart, statistics, economic calendar and news.
author: Bank of Thailand
